		<title>Valarian Raises $50 Million To Deliver Sovereign AI and Enterprise Infrastructure</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/valarian-raises-50-million-sovereign-ai-infrastructure/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 11:15:20 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[AI]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Startup]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[AI agents]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[artificial intelligence]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[NEA]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Valarian]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Valarian Defence]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Valarian Enterprise]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=203528</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>London-based sovereign infrastructure startup Valarian just closed a $50 million Series A funding round. Led by global venture giant New Enterprise Associates (NEA), this marks NEA’s very first defense and</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/valarian-raises-50-million-sovereign-ai-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal">Valarian Raises $50 Million To Deliver Sovereign AI and Enterprise Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">London-based sovereign infrastructure startup Valarian just closed a </span><a href="https://x.com/ValarianHQ/status/2076938840552411212" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">$50 million Series A</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> funding round. Led by global venture giant New Enterprise Associates (NEA), this marks NEA’s very first defense and dual-use bet in Europe. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Valarian raises $50 million just after its $20 million seed round. This takes its total funding to $70 million. The latest funding round saw a strong group of backers, including Lightbank, XTX Markets, Sequel, LitVC, and prominent angels Gokul Rajaram and Nikesh Arora. </span></p>
<div id="attachment_203531" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203531" class="size-large wp-image-203531" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Valarian-founder-1024x534.jpg" alt="Valarian co-founder and CEO Max Buchan speaking at a technology event." width="1024" height="534" /><p id="caption-attachment-203531" class="wp-caption-text">Max Buchan, Co-Founder. Image Credit: Valarian</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The startup, co-founded by CEO Max Buchan and Josh McLaughlin, a former US Army officer, will use the funds to fix a massive structural problem. While most governments and enterprises now rely heavily on American public clouds, they lack real control over their own sensitive AI systems. Valarian is solving this problem.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Securing Critical Workloads in a Fractured Cloud Landscape</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Europe’s dependence on American tech is a growing national security headache. Recent reports reveal that just three US hyperscalers control 65% of the European cloud market. In our new AI era, this reliance has moved from basic data storage into the core intelligence layer. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Many foreign governments and companies now worry about getting cut off from vital models at a moment’s notice. Geopolitical shifts have made these kill-switch threats feel very real. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">For agencies and regulated firms, true sovereign control is no longer a luxury. Valarian solves this by building a protective layer that blocks unwanted outside reach. It lets users run on major clouds while keeping total control.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/pixverse-raises-439m-real-time-interactive-worlds/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>PixVerse Raises $439M To Build Real-Time Interactive Worlds</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">How ACRA Wraps a ‘Sealed Room’ Around AI Systems</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203530" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203530" class="size-large wp-image-203530" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Valarian-ACRA-1024x572.jpg" alt="A sturdy, tan tactical transport case sits in the dark cargo trunk of a vehicle with a rifle visible on the left side. Text overlaid in white reads &quot;INTRODUCING ACRA EDGE&quot;. " width="1024" height="572" /><p id="caption-attachment-203530" class="wp-caption-text">Valarian ACRA Edge</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ACRA is the driving force of Valarian. It is Valarian’s proprietary control architecture. ACRA sits directly on top of Kubernetes, a popular system for managing modern software. It doesn’t require teams to rebuild their workloads.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Instead, ACRA places a secure enclave around every workload. This setup creates a dedicated policy stack covering identities, temporary secrets, and encrypted communication. Crucially, the customer holds their own encryption keys. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This means Valarian cannot access a customer’s system even if they wanted to. If an AI model or workload starts acting up, operators can instantly seal or revoke it in real-time. This quick isolation happens smoothly without crashing the rest of the network.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding round has gained high-profile support from top UK officials. AI Minister Kanishka Narayan publicly backed the company, calling sovereign AI capabilities crucial for Britain’s national safety. For investors like NEA, Valarian’s appeal lies in its software-only delivery.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/augmodo-raises-21m-expand-physical-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Augmodo Raises $21M to Expand Physical AI Platform</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Two Tracks: Valarian Enterprise and Valarian Defence</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This $50 million cash injection will help Valarian scale its technology in two areas. The first involves Valarian Enterprise. Valarian Enterprise targets regulated private companies running AI workloads with high consequence.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Valarian targets firms that need tight governance to meet strict compliance rules. The second area is Valarian Defence. Valarian Defence is built for nations and defense programs. Military and governments need absolute infrastructure control. Valarian Defence will provide that. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Under chairman Nick Trim Valarian is moving quickly to deploy its tech across four continents. Valarian offers the secure digital plumbing needed to run advanced AI safely. With the global sovereign cloud market expected to reach $80 billion soon, Valarian is in a prime spot to win.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/helsing-raises-1-8b-defence-ai-platforms/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Helsing Raises $1.8B to Expand European Defence AI Platforms</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/valarian-raises-50-million-sovereign-ai-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal">Valarian Raises $50 Million To Deliver Sovereign AI and Enterprise Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
